HEADWORD: gimcrack
<hw>gim"crack`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE., a spruce and
pert pretender, also, a spruce girl, prob. fr. <ets>gim</ets> +
<ets>crack</ets> lad, boaster.]</ety> <def>A trivial mechanism; a
device.</def> <rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A toy; a pretty thing; an ornamental object of no
great value.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> trinket, gewgaw, knickknack, tchotchke.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>  <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

